com.kuka.objectparameters

Interface IObjectParameterFactory


  • public interface IObjectParameterFactory
    Enables creation of object parameters which can be added to IParameterStructure or IParameterList.

    This functionality exceeds normal use cases and requires expert knowledge about the parameters that are being modified.

    The type is available through injection by using @Inject.

                                               String schemaId)

        This functionality exceeds normal use cases and requires expert knowledge about the parameters that are being modified.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of object parameters in the list
        Parameters:
        list - the list to which the parameter can be added
        schemaId - the schema id of a parameter to be created

        created object parameter
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the schema (of the schemaId) doesn't expose the right interface or if the list null

      • createParameter

        IObjectParameter createParameter(IParameterStructure structure,
                                 String key,
                                 String schemaId)
        Creates a new object parameter that can be put inside of the given IParameterStructure at the given key.

        This functionality exceeds normal use cases and requires expert knowledge about the parameters that are being modified.

        Parameters:
        structure - the structure for which to create the new parameter
        key - the key with which the created object parameter will be associated in the structure
        schemaId - the id of the schema that the newly created parameter is required to comply to
        Returns:
        created object parameter
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if any of the given arguments is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given IParameterStructure does not hold the given key
        IllegalArgumentException - if the schema with the given schemaId does not implement the interface that the given IParameterStructure expects for the given key
        IllegalStateException - if the given IParameterStructure does not define an interface requirement at the given key

      • createParameter

        IObjectParameter createParameter(String rootSchemaId)
        Creates a new object parameter.

        The resulting parameter can only be added to the IObjectParameters container of SpatialObjects.

        Parameters:
        rootSchemaId - the ID of the schema that the newly created parameter is required to comply to
        Returns:
        the created object parameter
